{
  "stem": "490.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a lovely city, and very much full of education and life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- so my sister moved-- lived there, and that's the only place I used to pass by, to see my sister, because she was not well off.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had a very big pleasure to see me growing up and the way I was.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so she was very happy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So-- and this was-- Actually, I was never in contact with these people before-- before the war, and even so after the war.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, we never met.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I left them when I was 35.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The only time I used to see my sister is once in a while.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they-- my brother did not survive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because it was-- they lived in the border-- right when-- when the war between the Russians and German broke out, they were right under firing line.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when they came in, they were not prepared.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When the Germans came in, they just slaughtered them all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The whole everybody.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody was left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my sister, she was at a border on the Polish side.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when she came-- she wanted to escape over the border.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Russians wouldn't let her stay there, so they sent her to Siberia, with her family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So-- and this was, at the time, it was the worst thing that could ever happen to anybody.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it turned out, this way, this was the only way she survived, because she did not stay on the firing line when the Germans crossed the border, because she went to-- to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And later, after the war, I looked for any survivors, and I find my sister, that she was in one of the displaced persons' camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
